</magazine>
</product>
</work>
</it>, <it><magazine wordnetid="106595351" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../306/886306.xml">
International Times</link></magazine>
</it>, <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../699/3500699.xml">
Frendz</link></it> and other underground magazines of the time) which he produces in his flat in <artifact wordnetid="100021939" confidence="0.8">
<street wordnetid="104334599" confidence="0.8">
<way wordnetid="104564698" confidence="0.8">
<thoroughfare wordnetid="104426618" confidence="0.8">
<road wordnetid="104096066" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../325/1150325.xml">
Notting Hill Gate</link></road>
</thoroughfare>
</way>
</street>
</artifact>
. He is aided by Alex Picton-Dinch (Rhind-Tutt), Hugo Yemp (Boyd) and Jill Sprint (Phillips), Sprint is also Purbbs girlfriend, or he thinks she is his girlfriend.</p>
<p>

The series delved into late 1960s culture and involved the characters in various ridiculous situations in this setting.</p>

